[49m[38;5;10m+      1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Recipe 13.10: Python Implementation Example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the federated clinical knowledge network concepts from Recipe 13.10. It demonstrates the mechanics of federation (source registration, ontology mapping, query decomposition, result assembly) using boto3 calls against Neptune, DynamoDB, and S3. It is not production-ready. Real federation involves governance frameworks, legal agreements, and multi-account networking that take months to establish. Think of this as the technical skeleton, not the finished building.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and a SPARQL client:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 requests
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `neptune-db:*` (scoped to your Neptune cluster)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject` and `s3:PutObject` on the ontology registry bucket
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `dynamodb:PutItem`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:Query` on the source catalog table
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `lambda:InvokeFunction` for cross-account query adapters
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll also need a running Amazon Neptune cluster with a SPARQL endpoint. Neptune must be in a VPC, so your code needs to run from within that VPC (Lambda in VPC, EC2, or Cloud9).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m These configuration values define the federation infrastructure. In production, these would come from environment variables or AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import datetime
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from decimal import Decimal
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from concurrent.futures import ThreadPoolExecutor, as_completed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import requests
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. Never log actual clinical knowledge content in production
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # since it may be derived from PHI.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Neptune SPARQL endpoint. This is your LOCAL institution's graph.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # In production, each institution has their own endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_SPARQL_ENDPOINT = "https://your-neptune-cluster.us-east-1.neptune.amazonaws.com:8182/sparql"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # DynamoDB table that tracks all participating federation sources.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m SOURCE_CATALOG_TABLE = "federation-source-catalog"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # S3 bucket holding shared ontology mapping files.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ONTOLOGY_REGISTRY_BUCKET = "federation-ontology-registry"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Maximum time (seconds) to wait for a remote source to respond.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Federation queries fan out to multiple sources in parallel.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # If a source doesn't respond in time, we return partial results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m FEDERATION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS = 5
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Maximum number of sources to query in parallel.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m MAX_PARALLEL_SOURCES = 10
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # boto3 clients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m s3_client = boto3.client("s3", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m lambda_client = boto3.client("lambda", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Register a Source in the Federation Catalog
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `register_source(institution_id, capabilities, endpoint_config, sharing_policy)`. Before an institution can participate in federated queries, it declares what knowledge it holds, how to reach it, and what sharing rules apply.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def register_source(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     institution_id: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     capabilities: list,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     endpoint_config: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sharing_policy: dict,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Register an institution as a participant in the federated knowledge network.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This writes a catalog entry to DynamoDB that the federation layer reads
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     at query time to determine which sources to contact. Think of it as the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     institution raising its hand: "I have knowledge about these topics, and
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     here's how to ask me."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         institution_id: Unique identifier, e.g., "boston-medical-center"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         capabilities:   Knowledge domains this source covers,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                         e.g., ["drug_interactions", "genomic_associations"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         endpoint_config: How to reach this source's query adapter.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                          Contains the Lambda function ARN for cross-account invocation.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sharing_policy:  Rules governing what can be shared and with whom.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                          Maps knowledge domains to access levels.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The catalog entry that was written.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(SOURCE_CATALOG_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     catalog_entry = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "institution_id": institution_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "capabilities": capabilities,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "ontology_version": "SNOMED-CT-2025-03",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "endpoint": endpoint_config,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "sharing_policy": sharing_policy,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "registered_at": datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "status": "active",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Write to DynamoDB. If this institution already exists, this overwrites
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # their registration (useful for updating capabilities or endpoints).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table.put_item(Item=catalog_entry)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Registered source: %s with capabilities: %s", institution_id, capabilities)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return catalog_entry
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Load Ontology Mappings from S3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `load_ontology_mapping(source_institution_id, mapping_version)`. Each institution models clinical concepts differently. This mapping file translates between the shared federated vocabulary and each source's local representation.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # In-memory cache for ontology mappings. In production, use a TTL-based cache
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # (like functools.lru_cache or an external cache) so you pick up mapping updates
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # without redeploying.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m _mapping_cache = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def load_ontology_mapping(source_institution_id: str, mapping_version: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Fetch the ontology mapping file for a specific institution from S3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The mapping file contains bidirectional translations:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - federated_to_local: how to express a federated concept in this source's schema
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - local_to_federated: how to translate this source's results back to shared vocabulary
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source_institution_id: Which institution's mapping to load.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mapping_version:       Version string, e.g., "SNOMED-CT-2025-03"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Parsed mapping dictionary with concept translations.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cache_key = f"{source_institution_id}/{mapping_version}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if cache_key in _mapping_cache:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return _mapping_cache[cache_key]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mapping_key = f"ontology-mappings/{source_institution_id}/v-{mapping_version}.json"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = s3_client.get_object(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Bucket=ONTOLOGY_REGISTRY_BUCKET,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Key=mapping_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mapping = json.loads(response["Body"].read().decode("utf-8"))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Cache it. In production, add a TTL so stale mappings get refreshed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     _mapping_cache[cache_key] = mapping
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Loaded ontology mapping for %s (version %s): %d concept translations",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source_institution_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mapping_version,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(mapping.get("concepts", [])),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return mapping
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Translate a Federated Query to a Local Schema
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *This is the query rewriting step. A federated query uses the shared vocabulary (e.g., SNOMED codes). Each source's local graph might use different identifiers or property names. The mapping file tells us how to translate.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def translate_query_to_local(federated_query: dict, mapping: dict) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Rewrite a federated query into a source's local SPARQL dialect.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The federated query uses canonical concept codes (SNOMED, RxNorm).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The local graph might store concepts under different URIs or properties.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This function applies the ontology mapping to produce a valid local query.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         federated_query: Structured query with concept codes and relationship types.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mapping:         The ontology mapping for the target source.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         A SPARQL query string ready to execute against the local Neptune endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Extract the concept we're querying about from the federated query.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     concept_code = federated_query.get("concept_code", "")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     relationship = federated_query.get("relationship", "treats")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     context = federated_query.get("context", "")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Look up how this concept is represented in the local graph.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # The mapping's "concepts" list maps federated codes to local URIs.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     local_concept_uri = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for concept in mapping.get("concepts", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if concept.get("federated_code") == concept_code:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             local_concept_uri = concept.get("local_uri")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             break
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if local_concept_uri is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # This source doesn't have a mapping for this concept.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Return an empty query that will produce no results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning("No local mapping found for concept: %s", concept_code)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return ""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Look up the local property name for the relationship type.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     relationship_map = mapping.get("relationships", {})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     local_relationship = relationship_map.get(relationship, relationship)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build the SPARQL query using local URIs and property names.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # This is a simplified example. Real federation queries can be much more
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # complex, with optional patterns, filters, and subqueries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sparql = f"""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     PREFIX local: <{mapping.get("namespace", "http://example.org/")}>
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     PREFIX evidence: <http://example.org/evidence/>
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     SELECT ?related_concept ?label ?severity ?evidence_level ?last_validated
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     WHERE {{
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         <{local_concept_uri}> local:{local_relationship} ?related_concept .
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ?related_concept local:label ?label .
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         OPTIONAL {{ ?related_concept local:severity ?severity . }}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         OPTIONAL {{ ?related_concept evidence:level ?evidence_level . }}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         OPTIONAL {{ ?related_concept evidence:lastValidated ?last_validated . }}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Add context filter if provided (e.g., "renal_impairment").
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if context:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         local_context_uri = None
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for concept in mapping.get("concepts", []):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if concept.get("federated_code") == context:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 local_context_uri = concept.get("local_uri")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 break
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if local_context_uri:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             sparql += f"        ?related_concept local:context <{local_context_uri}> .\n"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sparql += "    }\n    LIMIT 50"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return sparql
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Query the Source Catalog for Relevant Sources
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this part of `decompose_and_route`. We query DynamoDB to find which registered sources have capabilities matching our query's knowledge domain.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def find_relevant_sources(query_domains: list, requester_context: dict) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Look up which federation sources have knowledge relevant to our query.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Scans the source catalog for active sources whose capabilities overlap
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     with the query's knowledge domains, then filters by sharing policy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         query_domains:    Knowledge domains the query touches,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                           e.g., ["drug_interactions"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         requester_context: Who is asking and why. Contains institution_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                            purpose (clinical, research, quality), and user_role.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of authorized source catalog entries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     table = dynamodb.Table(SOURCE_CATALOG_TABLE)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Scan for active sources. In production with many sources, you'd use a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # GSI on capabilities or maintain a separate routing index.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # For a federation of 5-20 institutions, a scan is fine.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = table.scan(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FilterExpression="attribute_exists(capabilities) AND #s = :active",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ExpressionAttributeNames={"#s": "status"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ExpressionAttributeValues={":active": "active"},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     candidates = response.get("Items", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Filter to sources whose capabilities overlap with query domains.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     relevant = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for source in candidates:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source_capabilities = set(source.get("capabilities", []))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if source_capabilities.intersection(set(query_domains)):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             relevant.append(source)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Apply sharing policy check: does this source allow the requester access?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     authorized = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for source in relevant:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if evaluate_sharing_policy(source, requester_context, query_domains):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             authorized.append(source)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "Found %d relevant sources (%d authorized) for domains: %s",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(relevant),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         len(authorized),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         query_domains,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return authorized
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def evaluate_sharing_policy(source: dict, requester_context: dict, query_domains: list) -> bool:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Check whether a source's sharing policy allows this requester access.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Sharing policies map knowledge domains to access levels:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - "public": any federation member can query
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - "research_only": only approved research collaborators
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - "bilateral": only institutions with a bilateral agreement
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source:            The source catalog entry with sharing_policy.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         requester_context: Who is asking (institution, purpose, role).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         query_domains:     What domains the query touches.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         True if the requester is authorized for at least one relevant domain.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     policy = source.get("sharing_policy", {})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     requester_purpose = requester_context.get("purpose", "clinical")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for domain in query_domains:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         domain_policy = policy.get(domain, "public")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if domain_policy == "public":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         elif domain_policy == "research_only" and requester_purpose == "research":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             return True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         elif domain_policy == "bilateral":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Check if requester's institution has a bilateral agreement.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             allowed_institutions = policy.get("bilateral_partners", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if requester_context.get("institution_id") in allowed_institutions:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 return True
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return False
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Execute a Federated Query Across Sources
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *This is the core federation step. We decompose the query, translate it for each source, dispatch sub-queries in parallel, and collect results. The parallel execution is critical because network latency is the bottleneck.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def execute_federated_query(federated_query: dict, requester_context: dict) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Execute a query across the federated knowledge network.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the main entry point for federation. It:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Identifies relevant sources from the catalog
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Translates the query for each source's local schema
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Dispatches sub-queries in parallel
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Assembles and deduplicates results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         federated_query:   Structured query in the federated vocabulary.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                            Contains concept_code, relationship, and optional context.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         requester_context: Who is asking. Contains institution_id, purpose, user_role.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Assembled federation response with results, provenance, and metadata.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     start_time = datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Determine which knowledge domains this query touches.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     query_domains = federated_query.get("domains", ["drug_interactions"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Find sources that can answer this query and are willing to.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     authorized_sources = find_relevant_sources(query_domains, requester_context)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not authorized_sources:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "query": federated_query,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "federation_metadata": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "sources_contacted": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "sources_responded": 0,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "error": "no_authorized_sources",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "results": [],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Translate the query for each source and dispatch in parallel.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sub_queries = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for source in authorized_sources:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mapping = load_ontology_mapping(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source["institution_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source.get("ontology_version", "SNOMED-CT-2025-03"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         local_sparql = translate_query_to_local(federated_query, mapping)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if local_sparql:  # Skip sources where translation produced nothing
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             sub_queries.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source": source,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "sparql": local_sparql,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "mapping": mapping,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Execute all sub-queries in parallel using a thread pool.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Network I/O is the bottleneck, so threads work well here.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results_by_source = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     timed_out_sources = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     with ThreadPoolExecutor(max_workers=min(len(sub_queries), MAX_PARALLEL_SOURCES)) as executor:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         future_to_source = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             executor.submit(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 invoke_remote_source,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 sq["source"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 sq["sparql"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 requester_context,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ): sq["source"]["institution_id"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for sq in sub_queries
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for future in as_completed(future_to_source, timeout=FEDERATION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS + 2):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source_id = future_to_source[future]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             try:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 result = future.result(timeout=FEDERATION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 results_by_source[source_id] = result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             except TimeoutError:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 timed_out_sources.append(source_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 logger.warning("Source timed out: %s", source_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             except Exception as e:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 logger.error("Source query failed for %s: %s", source_id, str(e))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 timed_out_sources.append(source_id)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Assemble results from all responding sources.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     assembled = assemble_results(results_by_source)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     end_time = datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     latency_ms = int((end_time - start_time).total_seconds() * 1000)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "query": federated_query,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "federation_metadata": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sources_contacted": len(sub_queries),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sources_responded": len(results_by_source),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "sources_timed_out": len(timed_out_sources),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "timed_out_sources": timed_out_sources,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "total_latency_ms": latency_ms,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "results": assembled,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 6: Invoke a Remote Source's Query Adapter
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Each institution exposes a Lambda function as their query adapter. The federation layer invokes it cross-account via Lambda's invoke API (in production, through PrivateLink). The adapter validates authorization, runs the SPARQL query locally, and returns results with provenance.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def invoke_remote_source(source: dict, sparql_query: str, requester_context: dict) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Invoke a remote institution's query adapter Lambda function.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, this call goes over PrivateLink to a Lambda in another
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     AWS account. The remote Lambda validates authorization, executes the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     SPARQL query against its local Neptune cluster, attaches provenance
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     metadata, and returns filtered results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source:            Source catalog entry with endpoint config.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         sparql_query:      SPARQL query translated to this source's local schema.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         requester_context: Passed to the remote adapter for authorization checks.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of result objects with provenance metadata attached.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     adapter_function_arn = source["endpoint"].get("lambda_arn", "")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not adapter_function_arn:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.warning("No Lambda ARN for source: %s", source["institution_id"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     payload = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "sparql_query": sparql_query,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "requester": requester_context,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "request_timestamp": datetime.datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Invoke the remote adapter. In production, this uses a cross-account
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # IAM role assumed via STS, with the invocation routed over PrivateLink.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = lambda_client.invoke(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         FunctionName=adapter_function_arn,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         InvocationType="RequestResponse",  # synchronous; we need the results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Payload=json.dumps(payload).encode("utf-8"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Parse the response payload.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response_payload = json.loads(response["Payload"].read().decode("utf-8"))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if response_payload.get("status") == "denied":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Source %s denied query: %s",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source["institution_id"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             response_payload.get("reason", "unknown"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return response_payload.get("results", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 7: Local Query Adapter (What Runs at Each Institution)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *This is the Lambda function that each institution deploys. It receives translated SPARQL queries from the federation layer, validates authorization, executes against the local Neptune cluster, and attaches provenance. This is where institutional governance is enforced.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def local_query_adapter_handler(event: dict, context) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Lambda handler for the local query adapter.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This runs in each institution's AWS account. It:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Validates the requester's authorization
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Executes the SPARQL query against the local Neptune
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Attaches provenance metadata to each result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     4. Applies result-level filtering based on sharing policy
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the defense-in-depth layer. Even if the federation layer's
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     policy check passed, the local adapter re-validates. Belt and suspenders
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     when PHI-derived knowledge is involved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sparql_query = event.get("sparql_query", "")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     requester = event.get("requester", {})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Authorization check. In production, this validates against a local
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # policy engine, checks data use agreements, and logs the access attempt.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not validate_local_authorization(requester):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {"status": "denied", "reason": "insufficient_authorization"}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Execute the SPARQL query against the local Neptune endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     raw_results = execute_sparql_locally(sparql_query)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Attach provenance to each result so consumers know where it came from.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     enriched = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for result in raw_results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         enriched.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "data": result,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "provenance": {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_institution": "this-institution-id",  # from environment
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "evidence_level": result.get("evidence_level", "ungraded"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "last_validated": result.get("last_validated", "unknown"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "derivation_method": result.get("derivation", "curated"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             },
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {"status": "success", "results": enriched}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def validate_local_authorization(requester: dict) -> bool:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Validate that the requester is authorized for this query.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     In production, this checks:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Is the requester's institution in our approved federation list?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Does their stated purpose match our data use agreement?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - Is their access token valid and not expired?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     For this example, we do a simple institution allowlist check.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     allowed_institutions = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "boston-medical-center",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "midwest-health-network",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "research-consortium-west",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return requester.get("institution_id") in allowed_institutions
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def execute_sparql_locally(sparql_query: str) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Execute a SPARQL query against the local Neptune cluster.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Neptune exposes a SPARQL endpoint over HTTPS. We POST the query
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     and parse the JSON results. This must run from within the VPC
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     where Neptune lives (no public endpoint).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not sparql_query:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     headers = {"Content-Type": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded"}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     data = {"query": sparql_query}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Neptune uses IAM auth (SigV4) in production. For this example,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # we assume VPC-internal access without additional auth.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # In production, use the requests-aws4auth library for SigV4 signing.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = requests.post(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         NEPTUNE_SPARQL_ENDPOINT,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         headers=headers,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         data=data,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         timeout=FEDERATION_TIMEOUT_SECONDS,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if response.status_code != 200:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.error("Neptune query failed: %s", response.text[:200])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Parse SPARQL JSON results format.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     sparql_results = response.json()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     bindings = sparql_results.get("results", {}).get("bindings", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Convert SPARQL bindings to simpler dicts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for binding in bindings:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         result = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for var_name, var_data in binding.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             result[var_name] = var_data.get("value", "")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         results.append(result)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 8: Assemble and Deduplicate Results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *Results arrive from multiple sources. The assembler merges them, deduplicates (two sources might report the same interaction), and ranks by evidence strength and source agreement.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def assemble_results(results_by_source: dict) -> list:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Merge results from multiple sources into a unified, deduplicated response.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Two sources might report the same drug interaction with different severity
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ratings or evidence levels. This function groups duplicates by concept,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     merges their provenance, and calculates a consensus score.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         results_by_source: Dict mapping source_id to list of result objects.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Merged, deduplicated, ranked list of federated results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Flatten all results into a single list with source tracking.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_results = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for source_id, results in results_by_source.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for result in results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             result["_source_id"] = source_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             all_results.append(result)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not all_results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Group by canonical concept. We use the "related_concept" URI or label
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # as the deduplication key. In production, you'd normalize to a canonical
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # code (SNOMED, RxNorm) before grouping.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     grouped = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for result in all_results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Use the concept label as a grouping key (simplified).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Production systems use canonical URIs or code mappings.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         concept_key = (
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             result.get("data", {}).get("label", "")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             or result.get("data", {}).get("related_concept", "unknown")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if concept_key not in grouped:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             grouped[concept_key] = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         grouped[concept_key].append(result)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Merge each group into a single federated result.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     merged_results = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for concept_key, group in grouped.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if len(group) == 1:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Single source. Use directly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             item = group[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             merged_results.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "data": item.get("data", {}),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "provenance": [item.get("provenance", {})],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "consensus_score": None,  # can't calculate with one source
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_count": 1,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Multiple sources. Merge provenance and calculate consensus.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             provenances = [item.get("provenance", {}) for item in group]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Pick the data from the highest-evidence source.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             best = max(group, key=lambda x: evidence_rank(x.get("provenance", {})))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Consensus: do sources agree on severity?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             severities = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 item.get("data", {}).get("severity", "unknown") for item in group
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             unique_severities = set(s for s in severities if s != "unknown")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             consensus = 1.0 if len(unique_severities) <= 1 else round(1.0 / len(unique_severities), 2)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             merged_results.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "data": best.get("data", {}),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "provenance": provenances,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "consensus_score": consensus,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_count": len(group),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Rank: more sources and higher evidence = higher rank.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     merged_results.sort(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         key=lambda x: (x["source_count"], max_evidence_rank(x["provenance"])),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         reverse=True,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return merged_results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def evidence_rank(provenance: dict) -> int:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Map evidence level letters to numeric ranks for sorting."""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ranks = {"A": 4, "B": 3, "C": 2, "D": 1, "ungraded": 0}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return ranks.get(provenance.get("evidence_level", "ungraded"), 0)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def max_evidence_rank(provenances: list) -> int:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """Get the highest evidence rank from a list of provenance records."""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not provenances:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return max(evidence_rank(p) for p in provenances)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full federation pipeline assembled into a single callable flow. This is what a clinical application would invoke when a clinician asks "what do we know about drug interactions for Metformin in patients with renal impairment?"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def federated_drug_interaction_query(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     drug_code: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     context_code: str = "",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     requester_institution: str = "requesting-hospital",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     purpose: str = "clinical",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Run a federated drug interaction query across the knowledge network.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the high-level entry point that a clinical decision support
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     system would call. It constructs the federated query, executes it
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     across all authorized sources, and returns assembled results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
